  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "We planned Grandpa's surprise birthday party for weeks, and the date finally arrived yesterday, a Saturday, not a regular weekday.",
      "zh": "我們計劃了好幾星期，要幫爺爺辦一場生日驚喜派對，日期終於在昨天到了，是星期六，不是平常的上課日。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom sent me and William to a department store downtown to pick a gift, giving us a budget of one set amount per person to spend.",
      "zh": "媽媽派我跟 William 去市區一間百貨公司挑禮物，給了我們每人一個固定的預算。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William wanted to spend his entire share on candy, but I convinced him a proper gift shows more consideration than a bag of sweets.",
      "zh": "William 想把他那份全部拿去買糖果，但我說服他，一份真正的禮物比一袋糖果更能顯示用心。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We arrived at Sophia's house, the central meeting point, an hour early to hang balloons and a long paper chain across the living room.",
      "zh": "我們提早一小時到 Sophia 家，那是這次聚會的集合地點，要掛氣球跟一長串紙鏈裝飾客廳。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Upon hearing the doorbell later that afternoon, everyone hid behind the couch, trying not to be too noisy before the big surprise moment.",
      "zh": "下午稍晚聽到門鈴響，大家都躲在沙發後面，努力不要在驚喜時刻之前太吵。"
    },
    {
      "en": "When Grandpa walked in, we all shouted \"Surprise!\" so loudly that even Perry started barking with what looked like pure joy.",
      "zh": "爺爺走進門的時候，我們全部大喊「驚喜！」，聲音大到連 Perry 都開心地叫了起來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Grandpa said, with a broad smile, that he had honestly never expected such a big celebration for a typical birthday like his.",
      "zh": "爺爺露出燦爛的笑容說，他真的完全沒想到自己這種平凡的生日會有這麼盛大的慶祝。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The table had ham, potatoes, a bowl of beans, and one giant cake with a bow made of ribbon sitting proudly next to it.",
      "zh": "桌上有火腿、馬鈴薯、一碗豆子，還有一個超大的蛋糕，旁邊還放著一個緞帶做的蝴蝶結，看起來很得意。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia played some classical music quietly in the background, saying it added a highly proper feeling to the whole afternoon.",
      "zh": "Sophia 在背景輕輕播放古典音樂，說這為整個下午增添了一種非常正式的氣氛。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William and his cousin had a small kicking race in the backyard, using a bottle cap as a tiny, informal soccer ball.",
      "zh": "William 跟他表弟在後院玩了一場小小的踢球比賽，拿一個瓶蓋當成小小的臨時足球。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One guy, a neighbor Grandpa has known for years, gave a short, warm speech about their long friendship before the cake was cut.",
      "zh": "一位鄰居，也是爺爺認識多年的朋友，在蛋糕切開之前發表了一段簡短溫馨的致詞，談他們的長年友誼。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Grandpa said no gift could ever compare to simply watching all of us grow up, which made Sophia's eyes go a little watery.",
      "zh": "爺爺說沒有任何禮物比得上單純看著我們大家長大，這句話讓 Sophia 的眼眶有點濕潤。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William nearly swallowed his cake in one bite, and Sophia had to remind him, again, that food should not be a race.",
      "zh": "William 差點一口把蛋糕吞下去，Sophia 又得再次提醒他，吃東西不是在比賽。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Grandpa opened his gift last, and inside was a photo album of the whole family, which he said he would treasure for the rest of his life.",
      "zh": "爺爺最後才打開我們的禮物，裡面是一整本全家福相簿，他說他這輩子都會好好珍藏。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the end of the party, the cake was gone, the balloons had mostly fallen to the ground, and everyone agreed it was, indeed, a wonderful day.",
      "zh": "派對結束時，蛋糕吃光了，氣球大多也掉到地上了，大家都同意這確實是美好的一天。"
    }
  ],
